   ewheel=90921&sitesection=sechicagotribune&height=400&width=600

   Sungwon Choi, 14, describes how he and his mother escaped from their
   ninth-floor apartment during an early morning fire in Glenview by
   climbing down a firefighter's ladder. (Brian Cassella/Chicago Tribune)
   By Alexandra Chachkevitch Tribune reporter

   8:11 p.m. CDT, September 11, 2013

   Time seemed to slow for 14-year-old Sungwon Choi as he climbed down a
   100-foot ladder to escape a fire early Wednesday on the ninth floor of
   his Glenview condo building.

   "There were times I was so nervous I couldn't move," he said. "I was so
   high up in the sky."

   With thick smoke blocking their exit through the hallway, Choi and his
   mother were stuck on the balcony of their two-bedroom unit next door to
   the blaze. They yelled and waved for help.
